Key Match Events: Deniz Undav scored two first-half goals in six minutes to guide Germany to a 2-1 victory over Bosnia and Herzegovina.
Edin Dzeko scored for Bosnia and Herzegovina in the 70th minute.
Joshua Kimmich received a yellow card in the 90+5 minute.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Germany maintained top spot in their Nations League group with this victory.
The match was held at Bilino Polje in Zenica, Bosnia and Herzegovina with an attendance of 11,000.
